caption: Love this place.
Wonderful dinner with excellent attentive service! We all loved our apps, entrees and dessert. Will be back next time we are in town.

This place is great I love each meal we have had. However the menu is forever changing and nothing is ever the same makes taking children or college adults out hard. If you have consistent eaters or picky ones this is not for you.

Greatest restaurant in the Triangle hands down.  Bret Jennings is the best chef, an amazing sommelier, and a pillar of the Chapel Hill community.  Amazing staff amazing chef/owner and amazing food.  I would eat here everyday... One day I will 😊.  The best in the state in my opinion. Truth.

Classic fancy small-plate antics. Sure, we are eating ourselves to death and all, but don't come at me with children's servings of chicken and fish for $28. Only steak is worth that money per the oz. I gotta make this last til morning or spend more money on a 4th meal. So next time I'll just start with the wings across the street.
good food, good service, extensive and affordable wine list and good ambience. Tasting menu for earlybirds makes it a good value
Charming French restaurant. Delicious  food and excellent wine selection. We thoroughly enjoyed our  evening.

Cashed in a gift card from holidays. Outstanding food.  Flavor. Portion. Presentation.  Service good, they appear to work as a team and deliver tables when ready.  Free valet parking.  Thanks.
We've been a handful of times over many years and it's always a very good meal and a low-key excellent time.
So yummy. Got some really nice wine. The soft shell crab and beef carpacio apps are great.

Had the salmon.  Delicious with the black bean puree and guacamole.

Wow, I can’t believe I had missed this restaurant!Great food, ambiance and quick/courteous service. I had the three course meal (5:30-6:30PM). From bread to dessert, I did not go wrong. Valet parking was eliminated. Highly recommended!!
Gracious service, an inviting atmosphere, and exquisite food make Elaine's a must-visit.

Outstanding. I had the vegetarian entree, a linguine/mushroom dish. Friend who had steak said it was the best he'd had in ages, duck also highly praised. Attentive service. We were treated well even though some of us were probably underdressed (in uncollared shirts).
No true rating.  I sat out front and enjoyed the atmosphere and conversation.

Still great after all these years.  I came in after years out of town.  The chef and staff reminded me why it was my happy place for so long back in the day!

Delicious cuisine backed by lovely service. Highly recommend.

Elaine's is a rare treat in today's dining world, unbelievable food prepared very well , presented beautifully and served professionally by friendly staff. Excellent wine selection at good prices. Get a break from chain dining and treat yourself to great value and a nice evening out.
The Best place to eat in Chapel Hill! Go GT!
Duck breast could much better seasoned. Surf and Turf just OK. Nice ambiance.

Best restaurant on Chapel Hill.  Bistro menu and had the best duck breast ever. Venzuelan chocolate cookie with mint ice cream sandwich was spectacular. Deep wine list with lots of affordable choices.
Did not like the flounder with gumbo.  Too much liver flavored sausage and crayfish was tasteless.  Avoid unless you're a big gumbo fan.

This place is serious business.  It was a perfect father-daughter date from start to finish.  You will not regret Elaine’s...
Great place to celebrate~✓

One of the finest restaurant in Chapel Hill. Impeccable service, extremely high quality dishes that make you say "oh my!" every time, great wine selection. Perfect for a romantic dinner. Very expensive.

Very foodie type place. The fish dish are all excellent, and the bread is baked on site... Make sure to have the sourdough: it is delicious!

Good food, indifferent service. They made errors in the drink, entree, and dessert order. The staff was unapologetic and based on group size received an undeserved 20 percent tip.  Not likely to return based on other restaurants in the area.

Food was great, service was a little on the slow side.  This is an expensive restaurant, and the portions are small.  If you're in a rush, or you are very hungry, I'd recommend a different place.  Should be 4.5 stars, but for the rather long waits between appetizers and entrees.
Great flavors

molten chocolate cake very good.

Decent, eclectic locavore fare. We've been here twice; the first time was underwhelming but the second was much better. We were there for a late dinner but half of the menu items were twists on breakfast dishes, which was a lot of fun.

Came here for dinner with a large group from work. There was a set menu, but each course had 8 options! Food was nice and seemed fresh and locally sourced. Waitress was attentive but not pushy. A very pleasant evening.
Excellent food and great staff. They printed a special 30th birthday menu for my wife and had flowers delivered.

Brett Jennings and his culinary team do magic with the best local ingredients.  His winter menu is the best in the Triangle.
Excellent food and staff.  I have never seen a better service staff anywhere.

Had the best server ever, Arianne.  And the food and wine were perfect-recommend the ceasar salad and the oyster-spinach salad as appetizers.  For dinner the catfish and trout were splendid.  And the chocolate cake with caramel icecream, to die for.  All wine recommendations by server were spot on.
easily the most creative menu in chapel hill, but why put people on high chairs in the front window?
Great food, albeit a bit heavier than I care for on a regular basis. Terrific staff and adventurous menu. Service is always stellar. On the pricey side, but worth it for a special occasion.
